<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conference 861.00/292b:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-26T21:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">February 26,
                                        1919, 9 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>41. For <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">Bullitt</persName>. Please bear in
                            mind that the unjust imprisonment of Kalamatiano in Moscow and the
                            detention of <persName>Tredwell</persName> in Tashkent cause deep
                            concern and serve as constant source of irritation to American
                            Government. Choose the best opportunity to convey to the representatives
                            of the Moscow Government that this is a matter which will not be dropped
                            or forgotten.</p>
                        <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>